Process called "reset_all_animations" that takes manager as AnimationManager:
    Note: Reset all animations to initial state
    For each animation in manager.animations:
        reset_animation_to_start with animation as animation

Process called "reset_animation_to_start" that takes animation as Animation:
    Note: Reset animation to first keyframe
    Return

Process called "add_to_buffer" that takes buffer as CircularBuffer and data as NDArray.NDArray:
    Note: Add data to circular buffer
    For i from 0 to data.size minus 1:
        Set buffer.data.data at index (buffer.head multiplied by 2) to data.data at index i
        Set buffer.head to (buffer.head plus 1) modulo buffer.capacity
    If buffer.size is less than buffer.capacity:
        Set buffer.size to buffer.size plus 1
    Otherwise:
        Set buffer.tail to (buffer.tail plus 1) modulo buffer.capacity

Process called "update_plot_from_buffer" that takes streaming_plot as StreamingPlot:
    Note: Update plot artists with buffer data
    Return

Process called "auto_scale_axes" that takes subplot as PlotCore.Subplot and buffer as CircularBuffer:
    Note: Auto-scale axes based on buffer data
    Return

Process called "trigger_data_update" that takes figure as InteractiveFigure and data as NDArray.NDArray:
    Note: Trigger update callbacks with new data
    For each callback in figure.update_callbacks:
        If Collections.List.contains with lst as callback.trigger_events and item as "data_update":
            callback.callback with data

Process called "start_timer_callback" that takes callback as UpdateCallback and interval as Integer:
    Note: Start timer for periodic callbacks
    Return

Process called "register_brush_handlers" that takes figure as InteractiveFigure and brush as BrushTool:
    Note: Register mouse event handlers for brush tool
    Return

Process called "register_axis_link_handlers" that takes figure as InteractiveFigure and link as AxisLink:
